    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">An Application of Inventory Optimization Decisions among SMES in Auto Sector Using FCM and AHP Techniques</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Neelisetty Balaji</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">of Inventory Optimization Decisions<br />Auto Sector Using FCM</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Dec-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">T0069</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Small and medium Enterprises (SMEs) in auto component manufacturing
industry is playing a key role in the automobile manufacturing sector. The smooth
supply of auto components to automobile assembling companies is possible only
when there is a proper co-ordination and operational control of the component
manufacturing and supply of basic raw materials required for auto component
manufacturing. The nature of raw materials used in the process is wide in range and
in terms of nature of the component and its value. The short supply can also be
observed in many components. Some components require a special material or the
skill and the process technologies. These elements are not considered while making
inventory decisions by the bottom and middle level managers while determining the
inventory decisions using either deterministic or probabilistic and stochastic models.
The primary consideration is given to demand and supply in terms of quantity. It
means to say that qualitative factors are not considered while making an inventory
decision by the middle level management. But the final inventory decision will be
taken on the basis of some qualitative factors consideration by the top management
and implemented from time to time. Hence, the present study is focused in
identifying the what qualitative factors are considered by the top management while
taking inventory decisions among the SMEs in auto component manufacturing
industry in the auto hub state of Tamilnadu and with special reference to Chennai
region.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10117">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10117</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/6855">Ph.D - Thesis  </a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
